                            <comment id="13022408" author="tlipcon" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2011 22:56:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey Aaron. Sorry, one nit &amp;#8211; the renewal thread is explicitly &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; used for keytab-based logins:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (user.getAuthenticationMethod() == AuthenticationMethod.KERBEROS &amp;amp;&amp;amp;
          !isKeytab) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt; t = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Runnable&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the docs should not reference NN/JT. Typically the use case is for users running long-running processes which need to interact with Hadoop over the course of many hours without the user manually renewing the ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
